First time trying this stall.
The display of fresh taupok attracted me. So I ordered 2 fresh taupok in addition to the $5 small rojak. Total is $7.60 ie each fresh taupok costs $1.30.

One of the best rojak we ever had. The food ingredients were very fresh and not too salty. We bought the largest portion for $7 and we found the price reasonable. Service was very quick and aunty had a smile on her face which brightened our moods as well. This stall is highly recommended and you should definitely try it if you have not.

$4 takeaway - portion is so little. There are some rojak stalls in Jurong East with more portion and same price. Most likely won‚Äôt buy from this store anymore. Bean sprouts taste raw. The other ingredients are ok
